<br>
I've played EQ maybe 30 minutes the past week.<br>
When I realised this I began debating quitting.<br>
Gregar's post has brought me closer than ever. He reminded me of what it was like in the good old days, and what's missing from the game (for me) today. Even playing my twinks has become more of an exercise than an adventure.<br>
<br>
Awhile back, I was playing my mid-20s chanter, and got in a group of people who were playing their mains. They didn't know a lot. I didn't say much, partly because I was trying to get back in the swing of chanting (playing a chanter is *hard*.) It was amazing the places they didn't know about, the places they hadn't been, the &quot;for this you go here; that drops such-and-such&quot; that I took for granted that was news to them (no, I didn't blurt it all out, but it was fun listening to them speculate.)<br>
I was a bit embarassed because they asked me about my twinky items (BCR, Loam cap, that sort of stuff.) Like Gregar said, where I found them, not, can they have them. It was fun. I made 2 levels that day, the most I'd made in months with that char.<br>
I remember a vah shir I encountered who didn't know how to get to shadowhaven. I thought he'd just started a twink and wanted me to help the twink get to Gfay. Turns out he'd been told that Gfay was a good place for new players (which of course it is, but it's hellangone from Shar Val.) After talking awhile I realised he was a true newb, based on what he didn't know. Boggles my mind to think of the pointless lore I have crammed in my head regarding this game.<br>
<br>
<br>
Don't celebrate yet; I can't quit the rants section permanently, how likely am I to be able to quit EQ itself? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
